# Added Help Menu and Dialog

The Help Menu and Dialog feature has been successfully implemented according to Phase 37 requirements. 

## Changes Made
- **Help Dialog Creation**: Created a new UI component `HelpDialog` in `lib/features/dashboard/presentation/widgets/help_dialog.dart`. This dialog properly categorizes and lists all keyboard shortcuts and general application usage instructions clearly under descriptive headers.
- **Title Bar Integration**: Modified `lib/features/dashboard/presentation/widgets/custom_title_bar.dart` to include a new 'Help' `MenuItemButton` situated right after the 'Manage Setlists' button in the title bar drop-down. 
- **Dialog Wiring**: Wired the new 'Help' button to trigger the `HelpDialog` pop-up so users can quickly see a list of application shortcuts.

## Verification
- Verified that clicking the "Help" menu opens a well-formatted dialog pop-up.
- Verified that the pop-up includes sections for:
    - Main Shortcuts
    - Bible Search Shortcuts
    - SetList Shortcuts
    - Slides Shortcuts
    - General Usage
- Verified that styling adheres to the application's overall design system, using consistent headers and styled shortcut tags. 

You can run the application, navigate to the `Help` button in the top menu bar (next to Manage Setlists), and check out the new help dialog!
